 I can remember, because we went to church Sunday morning always, hail, rain, snow or blow and - me father - and I went to me father's and he used to cook the meal, the Yorkshire puddings and everything and when I went to Sunday school Sunday afternoon an
d I came back for tea, but we always had a light tea. We didn't have meat ever until after I came into Lancashire tea at Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 What was it, stewed fruit or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Well - yes - something, but always for supper we had cold meat and warmed up 
potatoes and I had me supper with me father. Then went back to grandma's. That was a regular routine right up 'til - right up to me leaving - I always had a day - a Sunday at home with me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 What about Sunday breakfast with your grandma, did she ever give you anything special?
