somebody in - Under - in Fadleigh actually and I used to take his dinner. Come home from school and used to take grandfather's dinner then come back and have my dinner. You know, the school wasn't very far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 And it would be a hot meal you'd take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh no, no, it just used to be sandwiches and - he had his meal when he came home at teatime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 What sort of a dinner would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh nearly always something cooked. Perhaps Monday, washing day, was - you now - perhaps potatoes or - cold m
eat or something like that Monday, but - other days was - well - I always remember one day was always sheep}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6118986\charrsid16738601 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
s head broth. But it was good - and dumplings you know. And - we'd - oh potato pie. Good cook. Grandma was a good cook. A good cook and I think when
 she was - in her younger days she was a cook in service. They came from, you know, the country and - there was nothing but service for them, they were up in the Dales and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 She was your father's mother was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes. Yes. Yes, she did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Had your grandfather been a farm labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, he was a dry waller. Yes, he came from Hawes in Wensleydale.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did he go round touting for jobs as a dry waller?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 I've no idea, because it was over when I - that was in his younger days, n
