\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did you do embroidery or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, only sewing. Only plain sewing you know and mending, darning, we used to have to darn, darn you know and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Do you remember ever going walks or bicycling or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, my friend had a bicycle when I was older but - no, I had no bicycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did you go walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 We used to go walks - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You and a friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Oh no, no, I - I never had to have a friend. That was one thing grandma never liked you know, you couldn't say my friend and I, it was always you know - we - we'd never to have 
- that - that was her idea all through her life, she didn't want you to have anybody to say - and if you mentioned mates to her - that was horrible word to her. Yes. So, you know - yes, she - she didn't believe in - going -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 So if you went walks it would be with your sister or auntie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh I didn't go often with - I went with auntie perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Do you remember ever taking part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh used to race. When we've gone in concerts, I've been in concerts you know. But that was at school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did you ever go swimming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You never played netball?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 While you were still at school in the evenings were you ever taken to any theatres or concerts or music halls or cinemas?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh - no, there were not 
many cinemas - I - I don't remember - actually ever going to a - a cinema or a theatre before I left school. And - the only things I ever went to were - were concerts at Sunday school or at the mission, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 It was never at a music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Never. The theatre was a dirty word for grandma. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did your grandma live you any pocket money, or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 My father used to give us pocket money but - if we wanted anything then we asked, we would have it but - we never had to - never
 had to take money if we ran errands. I'm ashamed to say it many a time but we - I used to run errands, there was an old lady lived at the end, we only had three houses in you now and she lived through the other side, and she'd ask me to go to the shop an
d - occasionally - and she would give me a ha'penny. And I can remember - not telling grandma about that ha'penny and going to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 She would have made you give it back would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes, I should have had to take it back. And - and - you know and I - 
it was as much trouble to me to take it back as to take it, so I never used to tell her. So how I felt like that many a time, it was wrong because it sort of made you deceitful. You tried not to be but - she never found me out didn't grandma.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 How much spending money would you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh about tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Was it regular every Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Well - yes, yes, I think - it wasn't a regular thing but she'd give - she was generous in that - or she'd buy sweets for us you know and Saturdays was the time we got the money you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 If you got tuppence on a Saturday what would you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Oh it would be sweets unless we put just something away if it was coming near a birthday or Christmas. But me father would perhaps give us a sixpence whic
h was a lot and we used to - I used to save that if it was anything big and it would buy a birthday present. That's how I used to save me money you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did anyone outside the home ever help your grandma look after the house or family, any relations or friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, I don't remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 If ever she was ill did anyone ever come in to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, we always looked after her ourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 So you don't remember her ever being ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh yes, I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 But you managed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes. Oh yes, I can remember grandma being ill, she broke her thigh and - but I was working then. I should be fifteen or sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 But no one had to come in and help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, auntie was there you see and - my - and I used to - she was a long time laid i
n bed. Actually she never walked properly again but - she was always there. That was - I should be older than that though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did your grandparents and father have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 I had a cousin, the cousin that took me out at Christmas Eve. Yes, she lived - even in the street actually. She did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 How much did you see of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Well - if - if - that was one of the houses I could go to, I was forgetting that but - oh I saw them - I could always go in if I wanted you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would you go perhaps every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
But she had a - a little girl and a little boy and - and I used to - now that was something, I used to perhaps just wheel her - her little boy out, that was something that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 So you'd be a fairly regular visitor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Yes, but I - I was - when I was eleven, that was at school wasn't it, I was one year out of school. I had an abcess in me neck and I was in Bradford Children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 s Hospital, and I was twelve months, I never went into standard four at school. I went from standard three to standard five. So that was a whole year that was actually I was to be looked after you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You were in the hospital?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes, I was in twice. I was in twice, I went in - can't tell you what year but I should be about eleven when I was in Bradford Children}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 s Hospital.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Was this cousin who lived nearby welcome at your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would she frequently pop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh yes, she would come in and see us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did your grandparents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Not - not too many, they knew quite a lot -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did they have any close friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Well - you know, everybody knew them, they were well known. Yes, they were friendly actually with everybody you know but I couldn't say that - they'd no friends sort of coming in to supper or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 So you don't remember them having any friends who would come to visit them and they would go and visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh no, no, no, no, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would your father have any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, father was very much a lone wolf was me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 So you don't remember any friends ever being invited into your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No. Only when relations came you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Just relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Well aunt - auntie and then we had a cousin at Pudsey and - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601 A}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 rncliffe 
cousins came to them and then when they came for - to stay with cousin at Arncliffe they used to make it a day and then they'd come for the day which was absolutely red letter for me you know. Lovely yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 They'd come for a full day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes, they'd come to meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 And you would visit them for days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Oh yes. Well I - I did, I used to go and stay a week with me cousin in Pudsey, she lived in a - a lovely big place. Her father - her husband was a - a - something to do with a flour mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 And you'd go by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Yes, I went for a week, I used to go for me summer holidays. It sounds awful, but do you know they were lovely and she used to - she'd such a lovely big lawn had me cousin Annie and I always remember playing cr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601 ick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 et on the lawn you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 But you don't remember any friends being invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Do you remember any friends or neighbours just calling in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh - oh yes, like - if anybody wanted any help any time they came. I can reme
mber them coming into the house then. Like one little boy was run over once and I was only very small then and he'd been run over and some - the district nurse was a friend of grandma's and she used to come very often and she came in one day and said this
 
boy had been run over and it was Sunday, he'd been run over and they were a poor family and immediately grandma made a jug of gruel - oatmeal gruel and sent me with it, and I didn't want to go home. Because I - I went to school with the girls you know and
 
it was a little boy that was run over and he was at home and - and I remember her sending - that's what grandma used to do, anybody that was poor or anything and - and I can remember her sewing bits of cotton, any sheets that had been worn and - and too b
a
d for sheets she used to keep and she used to them them round and - and make 'em into baby hapkins. Now then - and I can remember her having a pile in them - you know, if anybody was poor and - and - she used to send - she always used to send me on these 
missions and I never liked to go. I never liked to go you know because I felt like you know - they would think we shouldn't have done it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Was it anything to do with the fact that you weren't accustomed to going into other people's houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Could be. That - that could be. Yes, I wasn't so used to going to peoples houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
So people would pop in without an invitation but you don't think that neighbours and friends would ever be invited in for a cup of tea or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh no, there never was anything like that, no. Unless they were ill.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 So although your grandma wasn't over friendly with the neighbours she was thought of as being someone to turn to if they needed any help?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes, that was it, but she - she didn't -
 I never remember grandma going into anybody's house unless it was to help them in any way. She - she was - not - not one that ran in and out of anybody's houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 She sort of kept them at arms length?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes. But - I won't say that she wasn't frien
dly because - she must have been because when she was ill all - everybody came you know, everybody - we hardly knew where they'd come from, you know. Yes. Now that was - but she didn't - she didn't sort of - I never remember her going out anywhere into an
ybody's house unless she had to. That was in my time of course you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you; think your grandparents and father did when they got together with their friends or neighbours
? Did they make music together or did they play games together or whether they just talked, from what you say they didn't really have people in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No. No. Not - not - nobody came to stay, it was generally either business or - you know, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 What about when this cousin of yours came to the house, you say you'd play at bridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 It was always just the four of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes. Me sister used to come up and play with us sometimes, yes. But, no, no, she didn't - they didn't 
play cards. She - she would only call in casually would me cousin, she wasn't - you know she - she - we knew she was there and she'd perhaps call as she came back from shopping or something like that but - I don't remember anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Many people divide
 society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Group? Oh yes. Yes. Well - you know, there were people that - I think in those days you know, you - you look
ed - you thought if anybody lived in a bigger house or - or - you know, not having a motor car of course, they didn't have those but - you know, sort of - well the people that grandma used to go and - and - stay with were people that could afford to have 
a - a nurse for a month you know, and those people we thought you know were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 A bit better off?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Yes, and - I remember when I went to Gargrave once to my auntie, we were going to church one Sunday morning and as we went over the bridge my auntie 
said to me, now - the - the squire of the village was coming along in a carriage, now this is a long time ago, and - and I remember my auntie curtseying and - as they went by and I - I felt it was most amusing you know. And I asked her what she did that f
or, she said, well he was the squire you know and you all curtsied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 All the people in the village curtseyed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh no, she did, I couldn't tell you everybody else did but my auntie did and it was - that was the squire of Gargrave. I forget his name.
 I knew them in those - I didn't know them personally but I knew of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You didn't see anything of this kind around where you lived, only in Gargrave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No. No. No. But we were always sort of taught to be respectful to these people in our own place you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 The people that your grandma went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Could you tell me what the different classes were at that time, how you saw them, the names you would give to the different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 What would you have referred to the different sort of, lots of people as?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Well perhaps the mill owners you see - those were the people - mill owners were the people that belonged the chapel, the Bradford - the Eccleshill mill owners - were big people at - at the C
ongregational chapel that grandma went you know and - Mr Vint, that was Vint's mill and Mrs Henry Vint, grandma - she - she - she was ill and I think it was there where grandma went but not - but she - not with confinement but she was ill, she was older a
n
d grandma was sort of - went there to look after her for a spell, and so that was - but you know of course we thought they were - you know, you - you - they were the top people that's what you mean. Yes. Well they were - they were - 'cos they were mill ow
n
ers. And I only remember Mr - but he belonged the chapel and so we knew him quite well. And with grandma knowing him, I - I knew him too you see. But lots of people wouldn't have sort have dared to have talked to him you know. Yes. And - he occasionally c
ame but it were only for - on business. He wasn't for any friendly cups of tea because he's too far above you to offer him a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 He only came to see your grandma?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes, if there was anything belonging the church or anything to do with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Which class would you say that you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Well - now what shall I say - I don't know - I wouldn't say - we weren't definitely the lowest class you know - 'cos we never - you know, I think that's why my grandma never let us mix you s
ee, but we weren't - we weren't well off, we were just an ordinary people you know, there were - what would that class would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 What would you have called it at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 I don't know, perhaps - I - I don't know. Well I - I think - I think tha
t's why - grandma was a bit proud you know, and I think that's why we - we perhaps felt a bit better than anybody else, but we weren't really you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You weren't financially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh yes, we could have been financially a bit better because there wa
s quite a lot of out of work in that time you know and - a lot of poverty. But I couldn't say that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 This was in the immediate area around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh - yes. Oh well - not - not too much around our street but - in the suburb, not in the 
suburbs actually, more in the town where the slums were you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 They no longer stand now the houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 I don't think so now. Ours is still standing where we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 But the very poor area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 That - they were - they were the slums, exactl
y. That's one - one part of society. I wouldn't say they were very poor but they were the people that didn't care.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You think of yourself as being in between the very poor and the very wealthy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes, well - possibly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 What sort of people 
would you say belonged to the same class as yourself, what sort of people would you say that your grandma would approve of as being equal to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 What sort of jobs would they have, what sort of homes would they come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Eeh - well
 who did I know, I don't know. She always seemed very skeptical about everybody. But - we never had to - you know - I couldn't - I can't just tell you that time, I can't - the people that we knew mostly belonged - church and I - they were always a nice lo
t of people, you know, this -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Many of the people were church goers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes, yes, I should imagine that, well most -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Whom she vaguely approved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh she - she didn't - she - she never stopped me from going amongst them. I think perhaps i
t was that that - perhaps - with her religion you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You had to be respectful to the people who were employing your grandma?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Were - yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 And this Mr Vint who came to your house about chapel matters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh yes. Yes, he would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would you say that you were brought up to treat one sort of people differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 I think so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 But you were never told to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Or show respect in any way like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh no, no, no, no, we weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Was there anyone you had to call sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Never. I never called - unless it was - perhaps school master but not anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 So these people that you had to show respect to, you just had to be well behaved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Well - yes. Well - they 
were all sort of supposed to be the - you know, the top class and - perhaps we can be coming in touch with them through - through church. You see, the people that I cane in contact with were through our church. And quite a lot there that were pretty well 
off, well most of them were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your grandparents in these ways?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 In the district where you lived who would you say were considered the most important people by people generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Well - wel
l I should think - I can't hardly remember their names - the - now - well perhaps the - the people that owned the mills, they lived - one or two of them lived in that - Mr Henry Vint lived in - quite near to us and - you see they - perhaps I only knew the
m
 through - I only knew them through either going to the chapel or church and - I don't know, I think they - although - those people that - lived in the big houses and I can't tell you their names but - there was a Mr Whiteley and whiteley's mill, well he 
belonged with - Whiteley's mill. Now he lived in Eccleshill, those are the Eccleshill people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Why would you say that they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Because they were - well off in those days you know, they - quite a different attitude to life had people and what they have today.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You thought they were important simply because they were mill owners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Because they were well off. I think money talked actually then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You were impressed by it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes, I think that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Who would you say the shopkeepers associated with, who were their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 I don't think I could tell you that, I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would you know about the vicar, who he was friends with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601 
and who visited him at the vicar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 age and who he visited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh yes. Well - 
you see - the Vicar - the Vicar used to come and see us as well but - the one that came mostly to our house was - the Pastor of the Congregational because he came to see grandma and that was Mr Manning. The Reverend Manning, he was a Congregational Minist
e
r. But our Vicar, we used to go - I used to go there with the teachers, we had our teachers meetings in the Vicarage on - on occasions, in the nice weather we had garden parties in the Vicarage garden. And our Vicar was Reverend Mckee, was an Irish man. A
 very popular one, very popular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Who would you say their friends were, both Mr Manning and the Vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Well - well I think - I think everybody was the Congregational Pastor's friends because he was a friend to everybody. But our Vicar was - always
 very friendly but I think in those days, more so than now, that they - well - I think they sort of mixed amongst the higher class than what ours do today you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would you say he was a friend of the mill owners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Mr Manning, oh yes, yes. Yes. 
But our - our Vicar - well, you see, I'm always always talking about church but - that actually was all my whole life you know and those were the people I came more in contact with - our - our Vicar - well - I don't know, he - he was a friend really to ev
erybody but I think - in their own - he was in a sort of different class to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Do you think he sort of felt himself part of the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 I don't know. No, I don't think so, no. No, he was - he wasn't - he was - mind you that was - that was i
n - when I was older, when I was about fifteen you know, not - now, when I was younger, when it was - when I was quite a little girl our Vicar - I - I didn't know a great deal about him but he was a Mr Gleave and his wife was a very very - ordinary woman 
a
nd - and she was just like us. Now I can vaguely remember Mrs Gleave and she was a - a gaunt sort of a person but she strode about the - the place and - and you know you could go to her and be quite friendly with her. You didn't sort of put them on a pede
stal but that was - no, that was when I was a little girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 But did you feel in awe of Mr McKee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh no, not particular - not particularly but - they were always just that little bit upper class you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would you know who the teachers were friends with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
The ordinary teachers? Oh Miss - Miss Dene lived next door to me, she was a needlework teacher but I couldn't tell you much about any of the other teacher but Miss Dene lived next to me all my life you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Was she quite friendly with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes, quite food to us after mother died you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did you know any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes, well - no, our - our farmer, they lived not too far away, it was quite a - in the country you know, it was - it was a - it was - oh
 yes, well she lived at the farm, was at Fadleigh, she was our milk woman, a Mrs Jennings they called her for years and years. An old hardened farmers wife you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Who were they friends with, were they friends with other farmers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Well I couldn't tell you. I can't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You didn't come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 The employers such as Mr Vint and Mr Whitely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes. Whiteley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did they keep themselves to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601  themselves, did they only mix w}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 ith other employers or were they friendly with different people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
No. Well I - I should imagine they would sort of have their own - their own - bit of society. No, they were quite all right when you mixed with them in - the church work you see, but - as far as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 But outside the church work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, I couldn't - I couldn't tell you. No, we'd no idea - we'd no sort of access to anything they did, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Could you say that there were a different set of people who went to the church than went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 What sort of people went to the church and what sort of people went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Well - they were quite wealthy were the people that went to chapel you know. Actually I think both Mr Vint and Mr Whiteley were at the congregational and p
eople that - well - I couldn't just say - I always felt like that - you know - I couldn't tell you. Well the people - well as a matter of fact I never remembered talking to Mr Whiteley at all but - the - the other person, Mr Vint, I knew personally with c
alling on grandma you know, he always sort of would smile and we thought it was lovely if he smiled but - but church - oh they were quite well to - I should imagine a bit more aristocratic were the church people. I think they felt like they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Despite the fact that there were mill owners going to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Yes. Oh well - yes, but I think - in those days, I honestly think the religion and - and - and the church people felt they were one better off which was wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would you say there was any political difference in church and chapel people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Oh yes, I - well I think all the church people were Conservative and I think the chapel people were Liberal. I always said that. I think that is right you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Even the mill owners at the Congregational chapel were Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Liberals. Liberals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Well - I should imagine ther
e being - those that were in permanent work or - they were only ordinary working class people even the ones that grandma didn't care for us}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601 ed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601  to go play with you see but - the - o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
e particular family, his father - their father went around with a fish cart and - you know, in those days they went round with fish cart}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601  and - but they always seemed to have plenty of money but they weren't - they were rough. No you know what I mean, I - I - that's what comes to my mind because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 They weren't poor but you thought of them being rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Well I shouldn't imagine them being poor but the - they perhaps spent their money and he drank quite a lot did the man and I think perhaps that had a lot to do with it you know. He was nearly always drunk and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would you say that one group within the working class felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Perhaps they did, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Can you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No. No, because you see - father was a - a crafts
men and - and brothers were - apprenticed you see and - I don't think we ever thought them being any better than anybody else, even labourers you know but - I don't know whether anybody else did, we'd didn't - oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would you say your grandma and grandfather had the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Well - I don't know but - at election time - I mean - they had their own - you know, their own - grandfather was very strong you know and anybody that weren't - didn't just - see 
his way of thinking wasn't - you know - didn't - no - he argued, we had a man that used to come into the home sometimes because his little girl, his wife was ill and grandma took his little girl for a period while his wife went into a - consumption home a
n
d that man was a Labour man. Now it was the first - my first knowledge of ever knowing anybody belonging to the - it was the - it must have been in its infancy mustn't it. I don't know how long it is since it was started, but he was very strong. And he wa
s
 very strong Labour, they called him Mr Pell and he came occasionally to look at the little girl, the little - we had her for a period you know, just while his wife was ill and - and he used to come and - and he was - he was very - he more or less - he kn
e
w what he was talking about but you see grandfather knew what the was talking about and - there was great clashes and that was the first time I ever knew anything about the Labour party, but we were never - you know, never had anything at all to do with L
abour party. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 What did you think of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Well I don't know, I - I was always frightened when he came because they used to argue so hotly you know and - and he always kept very calm did this Labour man, always very calm and - grand - of course 
grandfather was getting older and - and he - he argued and argued. I can still remember that and I shouldn't be above eleven - ten or eleven then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 So the facts sort of went over your head?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes, I was afraid of - well he used to get right cross a
nd, you know, but he always kept calm did this man. But he - he used to - and he was a - a - definitely a Labour man, that was the first time I ever knew anything about the Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 From what you say your grandma didn't think many people were up 
to her standard so she would be the sort of person to treat people differently in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Yes, unless they - there was anything - like whatever class it was if they were in need she never - she never considered it, because as a matter of f
act she - she would help the poor - the poor people. That's why then - she used to make little things and send them, you know, to them or anybody came with any - any - which they did - she once nursed - a market gardener's son with scarlet fever and she h
ad to stay in the bedroom all the time, they didn't let him go home and - they lived quite near, the market gardeners and - they were Barkers they called them and she nursed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601 
 - she nursed that boy had scarl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 et fever and he was a year older than me, so he woul
dn't be - would only be about seven or eight or nine, it was after mother died. And you see, but that was - but other people, like the little boy that was run over was a poor lot of people that lived not near us really but the one that she me sent with th
e gruel. She - she didn't - there was nothing - it wouldn't matter what they were if she could help them. So that was the kind of person she was actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 So she didn't differentiate between classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No, no, definitely not in - in - anything wher
e it was needed, but she wouldn't have liked me to associate with the people that I took the gruel to. Is that - is that sense? Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 When she was needed she would help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 But she wouldn't take that so far as to be friends with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh no. It finished then you now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 But she wasn't friends with people who were much better off than you or was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh - yes, yes, yes, she was. She - you see she came across them didn't she in her - her work, you know, they - they we
re all better off than us because they could afford to have a monthly nurse in that time you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 And she was friendly with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh yes. Oh yes, those - those people that came. She wouldn't have them at home. She - they were always sort of kept
 at a distance. Because I suppose she felt she worked for them you know and - it's sort of an under - she always realized that she was their paid servant you now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Would you say that she saw herself as belonging to a particular social class or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 No I don't think so, I think she - she - you know, sort of felt she was respectable and - you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another and if so can you remember anyone who did do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Well - I can't - oh in one 
instance I can remember and it was - that would be when I was in me teens and a girl that I went to school with, she was only as old as me and she lived in a terrace just off our street, you know, they - the - their houses were rather nicer than ours, it 
was in a terrace and Mr Henry Vint the mill owners wife died and he married her. He married - and they called her Mortimer - Gladys M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2380354\charrsid16738601 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 rtimer and he married her. I think - I remember rightly - they'd been married a few years and then he divorced her because 
she went away with some friend of his. But she was an ordinary girl and she went with me to school every day. And Mr - yes - and she was only in her teens and he must have been fifty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did you continue to be friendly with her once she'd married him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 
Never - oh no, no, she never cast me aside. But - oh no, she always spoke to me but - even - after she married him you see I - we felt that - she was in that top class you know. I felt that but - I never passed her if she was in - they had a carri
age you know, horse and carriage, I seem to remember you know she sort of she always recognised me but I - I went to school with her you know. She never - but she did get -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 But she didn't retain friendships?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh no, not with most of them. She did get into the - she definitely went from one class to the top class you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 And she left him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes. She went off with -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 People who were equally well off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Equally, yes. She got into that class. And she - she - he divorced her. And sh
e - but she'd only be about - sixteen or seventeen, she was very young, a very young girl she was, she could have been a year older - she could have been a bit older than me couldn't she, Gladys. She could have been about a year older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Can you remember anyone being described to you as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Well I felt all of them - all of them were really you know that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Did anyone actually say to you, now there's a real gentleman or there's a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh - I don't
 know about them but - I think - yes, I had - they had friends - you see when I say they'd friends I don't mean in and out friends, I mean people that we thought friendly people you know. That's the district nurse, Nurse Bradbury, she was a - a - to my mi
n
d a - a - a real friend, she was a real friend to me was the district nurse, while - when I was a little girl. She - on a Saturday night, I'd forgotten this - occasionally, not too often but - on a Saturday night she used to go to the nurses home in Bradf
o
rd and - and she took me with her and I always sat in the kitchen with the maids and she was with the nurses, I can always remember them bringing me supper and it was such a - a lovely outing for me when she took me with her, and we had coffee made with m
ilk. At the nursing home, do you know, I can remember that and I was only little then you know. That would be when I'd come out of hospital so I should be about eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Can you remember particular people being described as real gentlemen or real ladies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Only these people that - like Mr Vint was a real gentleman because - they were the - they were the gentry you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Because of their standard of living?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Yes. Yes. And - yes, I think that was right. I mean, all those we thought were gentlemen you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12928801 GS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 Oh I can't think. I don't remember. No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2698416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4068123\charrsid16738601 You never remember your grandma saying to you when you were naughty, I'll call the policeman, or anything like that?
